Toy-maker Fisher-Price is recalling 83 toys, including Big Bird and Elmo, due to lead paint.
Mattel Inc., the parent company, issued a $30 million recall impacting American parents.
Concerns over Chinese-made products have led to increased scrutiny by the Consumer Product Safety Commission.
The recall has sparked demands for stricter regulations on toy safety.
RC2, the manufacturer of Thomas & Friends toys, is implementing lead testing on all paint batches.
Mattel has halted operations at the factory responsible for the lead paint issue.
The recall underscores the need for improved oversight in the toy industry.
